Ness Climbs to 3-Week High on a $5 Million Contract Extension

-- B y   R o n i t   G o o d m a n
-- 
2011-03-21T09:57:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-21/ness-climbs-to-3-week-high-on-a-5-million-contract-extension.html
  Ness Technologies Inc. (NSTC) , an Israeli
computer-services provider, rose to the highest level in three
weeks after it won a $5 million contract extension with toll-
road operator Derech Erretz.  The shares advanced as much as 3.8 percent to 21.20
shekels, the highest level since March 1. Ness traded 2.3
percent higher at 20.88 shekels as of 11:40 a.m. in  Tel Aviv .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ronit Goodman in Tel Aviv at 
 rgoodman9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
